"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168375","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-15","<p>There are 17 executive and non-executive members of the Department’s executive board of whom (a) 11 are male and (b) 6 are female.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-12-15T12:43:27.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168375/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168375/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168375/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-05","Directors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many members of his Department's executive board are (a) male and (b) female.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","217363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168376","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-15","<p>The Highways Agency estimates that approximately 2.1 million penalty charge notices will be will issued for vehicles not compliant with the charging scheme in the first year of operation. This figure encompasses vehicles registered within the UK and abroad.</p><p> </p><p>The estimated total of paid penalty charge notices is approximately £46.3m.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-12-15T17:17:10.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168376/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168376/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168376/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-05","Dartford-Thurrock Crossing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the number of penalty charge notices likely to be issued for failing to pay the charge at the Dartford River Crossing in the first year of operation of the Dart-Charge scheme and of the income likely to be generated from those notices.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","Mr John Spellar","217315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168377","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-15","<p>The number of reported road traffic a) accidents and b) fatalities there have been on the A14 in Suffolk involving drivers aged 21 years in each year since 2005 is shown in the attached table.</p><p><br></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-12-15T17:03:17.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168377/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168377/answer","217322.xlsx","217322.xlsx","A14 Suffolk","A14 Suffolk","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168377/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-05","A14: Suffolk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many road traffic (a) accidents and (b) fatalities there have been on the A14 in Suffolk involving drivers aged under 21 years in each year since 2005.","false","Biography information for Mr David Ruffley","Bury St Edmunds","Mr David Ruffley","217322"
