"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168396","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-11","<p /> <p>DWP Ministers have visited a range of organisations, including foodbanks, and discussed various topics, including welfare reform.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-12-11T17:43:45.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168396/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168396/answer","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168396/answer/previousversion/32887","Biography information for Esther McVey","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-05","Food Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Answer of 20 December 2012 to the hon. Member for Liverpool, Wavertree, Official Report, column 929W, on food banks, what visits Ministers of his Department have made to foodbanks in order to assess the effects of welfare reforms on foodbank use since December 2012.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","217484"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168397","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-15","<p>The information requested was not collated centrally by the Department. It was intended that all District Managers would write to their local Members of Parliament about Universal Credit national expansion, so that each hon. Member should have received a letter. Such letters should, as a matter of routine, be sent by second class post.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-12-15T14:33:24.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168397/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168397/answer","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168397/answer/previousversion/32874","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-05","Jobcentre Plus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to letters sent by district managers of Jobcentre Plus to hon. Members on 30 September 2014, how many such letters were sent; and what the estimated cost to his Department of sending those letters was.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","217486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168398","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-10","<p>At our request the Member for Angus’ office has shared the correspondence with us. We have spoken with the Head of Payroll Services at Shared Services Connected Ltd, and are now seeking an urgent case conference with them in order to expedite a response to Mrs Caldwell.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-12-10T14:33:59.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168398/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168398/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-05","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will instruct the Head of Payroll Services at Newcastle Employee Service Centre to reply to the letter from the hon. Member for Angus dated 3 November 2014 and the email dated 20 November 2014 concerning his constituent Ann Marie Caldwell.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mr Mike Weir","217475"
