"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167858","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-10","<p>The information requested is contained within the Autumn Statement 2014: policy costings document which can be accessed via the following weblink – the relevant page is 66:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/382330/AS2014_Policy_costings.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/382330/AS2014_Policy_costings.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","217122","2014-12-10T15:30:42.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167858/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167858/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167858/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate his Department has made of how many people will claim jobseeker's allowance as a result of no longer being able to claim the employment and support allowance (ESA) assessment rate when applying for ESA after being found fit for work.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","217121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167859","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-10","<p /> <p /> <p>This information is not available.</p><p> </p><p>It is not possible to calculate the proportion of those affected by the removal of the spare room subsidy policy to date due to the dynamic nature of the caseload (i.e. every month there are on-flows as well as off-flows). However a recent DWP ad hoc publication did show that between May and December 2013 around 19,000 of the caseload downsized within the social rented sector over this period. This is likely to be an understatement and it does not include those who have downsized to the private rented sector.</p><p> </p><p>This represents around 10% of all those who during this period were no longer subject to a reduction in their housing benefit award due to the policy.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-12-10T14:59:18.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167859/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167859/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167859/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","Housing Benefit: Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the proportion of people affected by the under-occupancy penalty who have subsequently moved into a smaller home.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","217111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167860","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-09","<p /> <p>Officials and ministers have had a number of conversations, during the policy development and consultation process, with employers who may be potentially interested in establishing collective arrangements for their employees. We cannot give details of the organisations concerned due to commercial sensitivities. We also sought input about the types of schemes that might be attractive to employers through our Defined Ambition and Collective Industry Working Groups.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-12-09T12:10:10.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167860/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167860/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167860/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent discussions he has had with employers on the creation of collective defined contribution pension schemes.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","217110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167861","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-08","<p>Statistics on the number of Employment and Support Allowance claimants are published at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistics-tabulation-tool" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistics-tabulation-tool</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users is available at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance</a></p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-12-08T13:13:01.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167861/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167861/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167861/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of recent trends in the number of people claiming employment and support allowance; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","217109"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167862","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-10","<p /> <p>DLA and PIP are very different benefits as PIP has more assessments done face to face.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-12-10T17:15:24.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167862/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167862/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167862/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 29 April 2014 to Question 195875, when he expects a comparable administration cost for personal independent payments to be available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","217100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167863","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-08","<p /> <p>The number of ESA claimants referred to the Work Programme has increased by more than half over the last 2 years and as such we would expect to see a consequential increase in sanction referrals as more people join the programme.</p><p> </p><p>ESA claimants are not sanctioned for not finding or taking up work and all activities claimants are referred to must be reasonable given their circumstances and capabilities. In any month less than 1% of ESA claimants are sanctioned.</p><p> </p><p>Evidence suggests that work and work related activity is good for people with health conditions. Through the Work Programme ESA claimants have access to the support they need to improve their skills and move closer to the labour market. With this increased support, comes increased expectations and where claimants fail to meet reasonable requirements, proportionate sanctions are applied.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-12-08T12:43:13.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167863/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167863/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167863/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the reasons for the increased number of claimants of employment and support allowance receiving benefit sanctions since mid-2013.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","217132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167864","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-08","<p /> <p>In response to the recommendation we implemented improvements to the hardship process in July 2014 which includes strengthened guidance for work coaches. All claimants will be informed about how and when they can make an application for hardship payment following a conditionality doubt.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-12-08T17:23:58.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167864/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167864/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167864/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","Jobseeker's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Government's commitment in its response to the Oakley Review, Cm 8904, to strengthen guidance so that hardship provision is clear upfront to all claimants who are sanctioned, what progress has been made in strengthening such guidance; and whether the planned implementation date of August 2014 was achieved.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","216998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167865","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-09","<p>Official Statistics on the numbers of New Enterprise Allowance mentoring starts and financial support starts are published quarterly and can be accessed via the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/pre-work-programme-and-get-britain-working#new-enterprise-allowance-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/pre-work-programme-and-get-britain-working#new-enterprise-allowance-statistics</a></p><p> </p><p>These statistics include a spread sheet with a breakdown by Parliamentary Constituency, which shows there have been 60 starts on the New Enterprise Allowance financial support in Stafford.</p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-12-09T16:14:45.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167865/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167865/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167865/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","New Enterprise Allowance: Stafford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Stafford constituency are in receipt of the new enterprise allowance.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","216975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167866","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-10","<p>In the WMS (link below) of 13 October 2014 the Secretary of State confirmed plans for the next stage of implementing universal credit to all remaining jobcentres and local authorities as we progress national expansion through 2015-16 and secure delivery of universal credit across Great Britain.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/documents/commons-vote-office/2014-October/13th%20October/17.DWP-welfare-reform.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/documents/commons-vote-office/2014-October/13th%20October/17.DWP-welfare-reform.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-12-10T14:57:00.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167866/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167866/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167866/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what date he has set for full implementation of universal credit across the UK.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","216982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167867","Cabinet Office","false","2014-12-08","<p>The factors that impact on household food security are complex.</p><p>In February Defra published ‘Household Food Security in the UK: a Review of Food Aid’. The report is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/283072/household-food-security-uk-executive-summary-140219.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/283072/household-food-security-uk-executive-summary-140219.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2014-12-08T17:23:00.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167867/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167867/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167867/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-12-03","Food Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent plans the Government has to undertake research into the reasons for the use of foodbanks.","false","Biography information for Lord Blunkett","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Mr David Blunkett","216993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167868","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-10","<p /> <p>DWP has outsourced the provision of its estate until 31st March 2018 under a 20-year contract with its private sector partner Telereal Trillium (TT), leasing back fully serviced accommodation, via a PFI Contract known as PRIME.</p><p> </p><p>The buildings occupied by DWP under this PFI arrangement are generally multi-storey offices and roof space is therefore limited, resulting in most significant heat loss being via the walls, which are predominantly windows for good natural light.</p><p> </p><p>As part of on-going life cycle replacement projects planned by TT, for windows and to recover roofs, the work is carried out to the current building standard which includes modern insulating requirements.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, during estate rationalisation DWP carefully consider the energy rating of a building as part of the decision process and where possible moves out of poorly insulated buildings.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-12-10T15:15:32.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167868/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167868/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167868/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he has taken to insulate his Departmental estate in order to improve energy efficiency; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","217054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167869","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-09","<p /> <p>We have a comprehensive menu of back to work support available, Jobcentre Plus’ use a range of innovative approaches to help older claimants. Local schemes include IT support aimed specifically at older people; dedicated advisers for those aged over 50; and help to convert dated qualifications into certifications that are relevant for modern employers.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-12-09T16:04:23.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167869/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167869/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167869/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-03","Employment: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department is taking to support people over 50 seeking employment.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","217023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168600","HM Treasury","false","2014-12-09","<p>The funding announced in the Autumn Statement is a down-payment on the NHS's own long-term plan, fully delivering the investment required to make the Five Year Forward View a reality in 2015-16.</p><p> </p><p>It also provides funding to start delivering the changes necessary to ensure a sustainable NHS in future years.</p><p> </p><p>This has only been possible through good financial management of the Government’s budget, and through the success of the Government’s long term economic plan.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-12-09T17:56:26.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168600/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168600/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168600/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-12-03","Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the implications for public expenditure control of the conclusions of the NHS Five Year Forward View published in October 2014.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","906528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168774","HM Treasury","false","2014-12-09","<p>I refer you to my earlier answer to the question asked by the Member for Stevenage (Stephen McPartland).</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-12-09T17:47:06.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168774/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168774/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168774/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-12-03","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he has taken to reduce tax avoidance in the UK.","false","Biography information for Jenny Willott","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott","906530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168775","HM Treasury","false","2014-12-09","<p>I refer you to my earlier answer to the question asked by the member for Inverclyde (Mr Iain McKenzie).</p><p><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm141209/debtext/141209-0001.htm#14120936000006" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm141209/debtext/141209-0001.htm#14120936000006</a></p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-12-09T17:45:30.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168775/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168775/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168775/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-12-03","Income Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent estimate he has made of how much the reduction in the additional rate of income tax to 45 per cent is worth for a person earning £1 million a year.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","906527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168776","HM Treasury","false","2014-12-09","<p>I refer the hon member to the Chief Secretary’s earlier response to questions 1 &amp; 12.</p><p><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm141209/debtext/141209-0001.htm#14120936000006" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm141209/debtext/141209-0001.htm#14120936000006</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-12-09T17:54:52.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168776/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168776/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168776/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-12-03","Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what fiscal steps he is taking to encourage investment in infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","906531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168777","HM Treasury","false","2014-12-09","<p>The government’s long-term economic plan is working, and the UK is expected by the IMF to grow faster than any other G7 country this year. Inflation is below target, the deficit is forecast to have halved as a share of GDP in 2014-15, and there are record numbers of people in work. But the job is not yet done and the biggest risk now to the recovery would be abandoning the plan that is delivering a brighter economic future.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-12-09T17:52:09.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168777/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168777/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168777/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-12-03","Economic Policy","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what progress he has made on his long-term economic plan.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","906526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167200","Department of Health","false","2014-12-15","<p>The Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority (HFEA) has advised that in the decade preceding 31 December 2012, the HFEA register records one incidence of a still birth following an embryo reduction at week 13 in a twin pregnancy, and one incidence of a still birth following a double embryo reduction at 12 weeks in a triplet pregnancy. Within this time period there are no other records of incidences of still births following foetal reductions in multiple pregnancies taking place within the first 16 weeks of pregnancy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The first trimester has been taken as weeks 0-13 and ‘early in the second trimester’ as weeks 14-16.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The HFEA has also advised that any records held on its register after 31 December 2012 are not yet verified.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-12-15T12:14:38.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167200/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167200/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-12-02","In Vitro Fertilisation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Wallace of Saltaire on 1 December (HL3088), what was the overall incidence of stillbirths from in vitro fertilisation pregnancies for the past decade following foetal reduction in either the first trimester or early in the second trimester that affected (1) the remaining twin from the same twin pregnancy, (2) one of the remaining triplets from the same pregnancy, and (3) both of the remaining triplets from the same pregnancy, according to data held by the Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL3301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167201","Department of Health","false","2014-12-15","<p>We have been advised that there is no evidence to suggest that mutations affecting DNA polymerase gamma result in high levels of the mitochondrial DNA mutations responsible for the mitochondrial diseases listed in Annex D of the mitochondrial donation consultation document. As stated in my previous answer of 17 November 2014 (<em>Official Report</em>, col WA59), mitochondrial donation techniques would only be used for patients that have an inherited mitochondrial DNA mutation and could not be used for those diseases in which faulty mitochondria arise from a nuclear gene mutation.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-12-15T12:29:26.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167201/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167201/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-12-02","In Vitro Fertilisation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answers by Earl Howe on 17 November (HL2642) and on 2 December (HL2905), whether they consider that mutations affecting DNA Polymerase Gamma might in turn ever be potentially responsible for disease-associated mitochondrial DNA mutations such as those listed in Annex D of the "Mitochondrial Donation" consultation document; and if not, why not.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL3302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167202","Department of Health","false","2014-12-15","<p>The Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority (HFEA) has advised that as stated in my Written Answer of 17 November 2014 (<em>Official Report</em>, Columns WA 60-61), when developing its policy on multiple births, the HFEA commissioned an Expert Group on Multiple Births after IVF (in vitro fertilisation), which concluded that the prevention of multiple pregnancies through single embryo transfer should be preferred to multifetal pregnancy reduction.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The evidence this recommendation was based on is outlined in the Expert Group’s report, available on the HFEA’s website at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.hfea.gov.uk/docs/MBSET_report.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.hfea.gov.uk/docs/MBSET_report.pdf</a></p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-12-15T12:15:26.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167202/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167202/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-12-02","In Vitro Fertilisation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Earl Howe on 2 December (HL2905), what was the empirical evidence upon which the Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority based its recommendation regarding multi-foetal pregnancy reduction.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL3303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167203","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-12-16","<p>The decision of the House of Lords in the case of <em>Parochial Church Council of the Parish of Aston Cantlow and Wilmcote with Billesley, Warwickshire v. Wallbank and another </em>[2003] UKHL 37 confirmed that chancel repair liability was a valid and enforceable property right. Before 13 October 2013 the liability did not have to be entered on the land register to bind buyers of registered land. Now buyers can be certain whether a property may be subject to the liability before they buy, helping them to make informed decisions.</p><p> </p><p>Information as to the number of cases parochial church councils have brought since June 2003 to recover chancel repair liability is not available and could only be obtained from court records at disproportionate expense. The Government is however aware that not all parochial church councils decided to register their entitlement to the benefit of the liability.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2014-12-16T17:09:44.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167203/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167203/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167203/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-12-02","Churches: Repairs and Maintenance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many court cases have been brought by parochial church councils to recover chancel repair liability since the Aston Cantlow judgment by the House of Lords in 2003.","false","Biography information for Lord Avebury",,"Lord Avebury","HL3304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167204","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-10","<p>The Government is aware that the Government of Bangladesh has approved the draft Foreign Donations Act (FDA) to go to Parliament. We are following the development of the new legislation closely. The Government, EU and other like-minded partners raised our concerns over restricting civil society with the Government of Bangladesh during the drafting of the Act. This included the Department for International Development (DfID) Country Representative leading a delegation to report donors’ concerns over aspects of the Act.</p><p> </p><p>During the meeting between the Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), and the Bangladesh Prime Minister in July, both agreed on the importance of an open society and political system in which democratic political participation and media freedoms are respected. Most recently in October, the former DfID Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State, my right hon. Friend the Member for Hornsey and Wood Green (Lynne Featherstone), set out UK concerns on the FDA during her visit to Bangladesh, stressing that the Act risked penalising genuine donor and civil society activity.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2014-12-10T14:29:02.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167204/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167204/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-12-02","Bangladesh","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they and the European Union High Representative on Foreign Affairs respectively have made to the government of Bangladesh about its Foreign Donations (Voluntary Activities) Regulation Bill 2014.","false","Biography information for Lord Avebury",,"Lord Avebury","HL3305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167205","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-08","<p>Last year’s review of our 2011 HIV Position Paper highlighted integrated responses to tackling HIV and tuberculosis co-infection as a key area of current and on-going work.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>DFID health advisers are aware of the package of collaborative TB and HIV activities recommended by WHO and are able to discuss these with the TB and HIV control programmes in the countries we support. However due to our current financial and management information systems we are unable to report on the specific interventions requested without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Increasingly the Global Fund is the main financing mechanism for the UK’s support to TB and HIV. DFID has been strongly involved in the recent Global Fund requirement for countries burdened by the two diseases to put forward a unified and integrated application for joint TB-HIV programmes.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Northover","HL3307 ; HL3308 ; HL3309","2014-12-08T12:17:06.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167205/answer","Biography information for Baroness Northover","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167205/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Developing Countries: HIV Infection","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many of the Department for International Development's bilateral HIV programmes actively incorporate (1) screening for, and (2) diagnosis of, tuberculosis.","false","Biography information for Baroness Nye",,"Baroness Nye","HL3306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167206","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-08","<p>Last year’s review of our 2011 HIV Position Paper highlighted integrated responses to tackling HIV and tuberculosis co-infection as a key area of current and on-going work.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>DFID health advisers are aware of the package of collaborative TB and HIV activities recommended by WHO and are able to discuss these with the TB and HIV control programmes in the countries we support. However due to our current financial and management information systems we are unable to report on the specific interventions requested without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Increasingly the Global Fund is the main financing mechanism for the UK’s support to TB and HIV. DFID has been strongly involved in the recent Global Fund requirement for countries burdened by the two diseases to put forward a unified and integrated application for joint TB-HIV programmes.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Northover","HL3306 ; HL3308 ; HL3309","2014-12-08T12:17:06.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167206/answer","Biography information for Baroness Northover","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167206/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Developing Countries: HIV Infection","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many of the Department for International Development's bilateral HIV programmes seek to prevent tuberculosis among people living with HIV through (1) infection control, (2) active case finding, and (3) initiation of preventative therapies.","false","Biography information for Baroness Nye",,"Baroness Nye","HL3307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167207","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-08","<p>Last year’s review of our 2011 HIV Position Paper highlighted integrated responses to tackling HIV and tuberculosis co-infection as a key area of current and on-going work.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>DFID health advisers are aware of the package of collaborative TB and HIV activities recommended by WHO and are able to discuss these with the TB and HIV control programmes in the countries we support. However due to our current financial and management information systems we are unable to report on the specific interventions requested without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Increasingly the Global Fund is the main financing mechanism for the UK’s support to TB and HIV. DFID has been strongly involved in the recent Global Fund requirement for countries burdened by the two diseases to put forward a unified and integrated application for joint TB-HIV programmes.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Northover","HL3306 ; HL3307 ; HL3309","2014-12-08T12:17:06.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167207/answer","Biography information for Baroness Northover","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167207/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Developing Countries: HIV Infection","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to ensure that the HIV and tuberculosis co-ordinating bodies in countries where the Department for International Development has a bilateral HIV programme are (1) developing integrated tuberculosis and HIV services, and (2) carrying out joint tuberculosis and HIV planning.","false","Biography information for Baroness Nye",,"Baroness Nye","HL3308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167208","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-08","<p>Last year’s review of our 2011 HIV Position Paper highlighted integrated responses to tackling HIV and tuberculosis co-infection as a key area of current and on-going work.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>DFID health advisers are aware of the package of collaborative TB and HIV activities recommended by WHO and are able to discuss these with the TB and HIV control programmes in the countries we support. However due to our current financial and management information systems we are unable to report on the specific interventions requested without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Increasingly the Global Fund is the main financing mechanism for the UK’s support to TB and HIV. DFID has been strongly involved in the recent Global Fund requirement for countries burdened by the two diseases to put forward a unified and integrated application for joint TB-HIV programmes.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Northover","HL3306 ; HL3307 ; HL3308","2014-12-08T12:17:07.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167208/answer","Biography information for Baroness Northover","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167208/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Developing Countries: HIV Infection","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the remarks by the Secretary of State for International Development on 5 March (HC Deb, col 879), what is the timeframe for integrating collaborative tuberculosis and HIV activities into all Department for International Development HIV programmes.","false","Biography information for Baroness Nye",,"Baroness Nye","HL3309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167209","Department of Health","false","2014-12-16","<p>Local National Health Service clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) are responsible for funding the majority of acute and community services. NHS England sets CCG funding allocations but does not direct CCGs in how those funds should be applied between different services. The in-year reporting of CCG expenditure does not provide the fine detail on movements in expenditure between acute services and community services. However, the NHS does produce programme budgeting data on historical expenditure which provides information on expenditure by major health condition as well as, for last three years, a breakdown by care-setting. The data on expenditure by care-settings is relatively new and is not yet considered robust enough to make comparisons of expenditure by care-setting. The 2013-14 data will be available in 2015, under a revised format.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-12-16T16:28:02.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167209/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167209/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167209/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-12-02","NHS: Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much money they have redirected from acute services to community services in England, for example through community provision for people with severe learning difficulties; and how much money is flowing in the opposite direction.","false","Biography information for Lord Mawson",,"Lord Mawson","HL3310"
